{
  "doc_id": "27408",
  "text": "In order to understand similarities and differences of vegetation on the mounds and in the forest near the savanna (pampa) edge, two r-hectare inventories associated with Ibibate Mound Complex and its immediate environs were carried out. These inventories are referred to as the Mound Inventory and the Pampa Inventory. The methods employed in this study follow largely those explained in [CITATION_1] Campbell and colleagues 1986 (and Campbell et al., chapter I, this is zigzag in shape. It was not feasible to layout a narrow rectangular inventory inside the single forest type in this area, but the roo-by-roo-meter inventory did cover and stay within the boundaries of this single forest type.",
